metadata.title: AI Coding Challenge Reveals Low Scores
metadata.description: The K Prize is a new AI coding competition created by Andy Konwinski to provide a clean benchmark, free from data contamination. Its first results revealed a surprisingly low top score of 7.5%, showing a clear gap between AI’s real coding ability and industry hype. Konwinski has offered a large reward for any open-source model that scores above 90%, emphasizing the need for tougher, unbiased tests.
